{"title": "2020-02-12 Microbe-drought/insect-plant interactions", "author": null, "url": "https://www.pflanzenforschung.de/de/service/stellenanzeigen/2020-02-12-microbe-droughtinsect-plant-interactions", "hostname": "pflanzenforschung.de", "description": null, "sitename": "Pflanzenforschung.de", "date": "2020-02-12", "id": null, "license": null, "body": null, "comments": "", "commentsbody": null, "raw_text": null, "text": "Doktorand/PhD\nMicrobe-drought/insect-plant interactions\nStellenanangebot Doktorand/PhD in Wageningen | Niederlande\nStellenbeschreibung\n|Location:||Wageningen|\n|Hours:||38|\n|Function|\n|Do you want to unravel how the below-ground microbiome alleviates drought stress and insect herbivory in plants? And would you like to work as a PhD candidate in an international, multidisciplinary team?\n|\nWe are looking for a talented PhD candidate in the field of plant physiology and plant-microbe-insect interactions, who is interested in molecular mechanisms underlying drought tolerance and insect resistance in cruciferous plants. You will study plant-growth promoting rhizobacteria for their stress-protective properties against drought and herbivorous insects with the aim to identify the molecular mechanisms and signaling pathways underlying these interactions. You will focus on transcriptome analysis and the discovery of plant genes and processes that are crucial for plants to maximize profitable functions from their root microbiome and help the plant to perform better under environmental stresses.\nYou will be working in at the Laboratory of Plant Physiology and the Laboratory of Entomology, while being closely connected to a multidisciplinary team of PhD students, post-docs and principal investigators at 5 academic institutes.\nThis research project addresses fundamental research to provide a basis for innovative developments in sustainable crop protection based on plant capacities to defend themselves against stresses.\n|Function Requirements|\n|\n|\n|Working conditions|\n|We offer a full-time position (38 hours), initially for 1 year after which a go/no go decision will be taken on extension with another three years. Gross salary per month \u20ac 2325,- in the first year rising to \u20ac 2972,- per month in the fourth year, for a fulltime appointment. The candidate will be based at the Laboratory of Entomology in Wageningen.\n|\nIn addition, we offer:\nWe offer a versatile job in an international environment with varied activities in a pleasant and open working atmosphere.\n|Contactinformation|\n|For more information about this function, please contact Professor Marcel Dicke,\n|\nFor more information about the procedure, please contact .\nGeneral information about the Laboratory of Entomology can be found on\nGeneral information about the Laboratory of Plant Physiology can be found on\nThis vacancy is open up to and including March 15, 2020.\nYou can only apply online through:\nThe first job interviews will take place in the week of March 23, 2020.\nWith approximately 30 locations, 6,000 employees, and 12,000 students, Wageningen University & Research is one of the leading organisations in its domain worldwide. An integrated approach to problems and the cooperation between various disciplines are at the heart of the unique approach of Wageningen.\nFor further information about working at Wageningen University & Research, take a look at\n[the](http://www.wageningenur.nl/career) [special career site](http://www.wur.nl/en/Jobs.htm).\nEqual opportunities employer\nWe are an equal opportunities employer and welcome applications from all suitably qualified persons regardless of their race, sex, disability, religion/belief, sexual orientation or age.", "language": null, "image": null, "pagetype": "article", "links": ["/", "http://www.bmbf.de", "https://www.pflanzenforschung.de/de/home", "javascript:;", "https://www.pflanzenforschung.de/de/pflanzenwissen/journal", "https://www.pflanzenforschung.de/de/pflanzenwissen/ext